utterances.utterance: And now a review of a wretched thing called "The View." They've been scoring some big names lately. utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Please observe.

utterances.speaker: WHOOPI GOLDBERG, ABC HOST
utterances.utterance: Please welcome activist and co-author of the book "Gutsy Women" and pretty good girl woman in her own right. Chelsea Clinton.

utterances.speaker: C. CLINTON
utterances.utterance: Thank you.

utterances.speaker: GOLDBERG
utterances.utterance: The son of the gentleman in the White House. DJT.

utterances.utterance: You did something that triggered a lot of people yesterday, including myself by releasing the name of the whistleblower. That's something that dictators do.

utterances.speaker: C. CLINTON
utterances.utterance: Thank you.

utterances.utterance: You have got some big fans back there. I see you, ma'am. They love you.

utterances.utterance: Congratulations on the book. It's really a terrific book.

utterances.speaker: GOLDBERG

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Oh my god. Yes, maybe it's me, but I think they're a teensy weensy biased.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: But hey, it's "The View," otherwise known as a knitting circle of hell. Personally, I'd rather watch my Aunt Doris dominate a game of cornhole.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Hell, yes, Doris. That's "The View," Tyrus. I like to look at - -

utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.utterance: Come on my show and we will boo you out the building before you even get started. utterances.utterance: Meaning, seriously, you only live longer by comparison because conscientious people like me are dying sooner. utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: First one there. Scott, you know, your book "Loserthink" you cover a lot of habits of very successful people. I actually show up at airports before some of them are open.

utterances.utterance: I was wondering about this story because I was late to two interviews yesterday and it didn't make me happy. Now I realized, I think I'm doing it wrong.

utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.utterance: I am making it worse. Cakes, pastries.

utterances.utterance: Yes, Dave. Does this bother you? It just means -- it just means narcissistic careless people are happier. Right?

utterances.utterance: Yes, but I guess that makes sense, because if you're not burdened by, you know, like the fact that you're, you know, putting everybody else out then you're probably going to have a pretty happy life.
